{"address":"0x75ee6eb3d8dacf41ee2e5307090b197d3e1cca6e","signedPayload":"{
	"for": "nouns-agora",
	"delegateStatement": "![](https://i.imgur.com/cEKQzYk.png)\n\nHi, this is [Noun 22](https://nouns.wtf/noun/22).\n\n### Who am I?\nAfter joining Nouns DAO in the first month of the project‚Äôs inception, I have been fortunate enough to have the DAO‚Äôs support to be compensated to work for the DAO in a variety of roles.\n\n**[Proposal 111](https://nouns.wtf/vote/111) contains a detailed overview both my current role & history in the DAO.**\n\nIn addition to being a delegate, I am currently a Core Contributor for the Nouns DAO protocol, where my responsibilties include:\n\n* Leading the NSFW (formerly Small Grants) pod ([Overview](https://i.imgur.com/BIlJyos.png) / [Funding History](https://maty-eth.notion.site/68f80b714b8e49b29c43527fd5ebe0e8?v=31ab66c0c24d470dadef8a8dbb2533a1))\n* Community Builder - onboarding new DAO members, hosting the weekly Nouner Town Hall call, and handling other organizational and administrative matters.\n\nI own 2 Nouns, and the rest of my votes come from delegations. My role as delegate started when I asked inactive DAO memebrs to delegate me their vote over the summer, and today **I am one of the largest delegates in the DAO.**\n\n### My Philosophy on Delegation\nSimply put, as exciting and fun as it is to work on Nouns, governance is work. I have been fortunate enough to be able to spend the majority of my time working on Nouns, and be compensated to do so by the DAO, for over a year.\n\nI do this because I think that Nouns is the single most exciting project going on in crypto today. I have had a front row seat to watch this DAO grow, change, and evolve over the last year. Our decentralized organization has rapidly scaled, not just in the number members, but in the overall project scope and diversity of opinion of Nouners. Whereas a year ago there used to be quiet days where not much happened, it is now challenging to keep up with every channel in the Discord these days.\n\nAs the DAO‚Äôs growth accelerates, keeping up on everything that is going on in the DAO is effectively a full time job.\n\nMost Nouners are extremely successful and busy people. That, combined with the scale and complexity of everything that happens day to day, makes it unrealistic to expect that all Nouners will have the time to make informed decisions on every matter in the DAO.\n\nFor that reason, I would like to offer my services as a delegate to any Noun owner. I have been one of the most active members of this DAO since inception, and **as your delegate, I will steward your vote in the best interests of both Nouns DAO and the future value of your investment.**\n\n### Positions\nI support [Nounish](https://i.imgur.com/X5fWj6W.png) builders and proposals. I encourage passion and authenticity - I want to let people who are inspired by nouns be unrestrained to build out their vision. Nouns is CC0 and permissionless by design.\n\nNounishness is an emergent value set, and we are best served by letting people enjoy and adopt it however they wish, and encouraging passionaite creatives to build their Nounish vision however they want.\n\nYES:\n\n* User generated content - podcasts, twitter spaces, contests\n* Internet-native content - viral videos, social media, memes\n* Builders - technical tools, analytics, data, AI\n* Public Goods - making the world a better place\n* Ubiquity and ambiguity of the meme - Nouns is an emergent value set. Think of [Shepard Fairey‚Äôs OBEY posters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andre_the_Giant_Has_a_Posse) as an influence\n* Finding talented contributors, leaning into building the relationship, and scaling up their contributions\n* Negotiating costs with contributors and holding them accountible (without micro-managing)\n\nNO:\n\n* Generic copy/paste sponsorships, even if they are a fair deal\n* Expensive proposals backed up only by credentials.\n* Expensive proposals in legacy industries where the cost is justified by the proposer as being ‚Äújust the way things are done.‚Äù",
